name: Stilts
description:
Digital Photography

A photo taken just after sunset, final glimpses of an area that had been home for months. As a nomadic soul, it's become normal to pack up and leave without looking back. This time was different. After spending the longest span of time anywhere in over 5 years, it only felt natural to look back, literally and figuratively. "Stilts" represents for me the thoughtful contemplative nature of the sun setting and night encroaching, and the reflections of the solitude of constantly being on the move. The pictured lake-house may seem stable, but when the storms come, its lack of a foundation will eventually lead to its downfall. 

How can we stand the test of time without healthy roots?
